issue.title: [chore] Remove TOC in README
issue.body:
The readme currently has a TOC defined. This is nice, but github provides a TOC feature out of the box:
https://github.blog/changelog/2021-04-13-table-of-contents-support-in-markdown-files/

I don't think most people know about this, but it is a nice feature that is available out of the box.

Maybe we should remove the TOC in our README to clean things up?

comment.body:
This also brings up some other documentation "gaps" I saw while refreshing myself on how this works overall.

Most of the contributing docs for feeCodeCamp are oriented toward the core curriculum, or other things like translations. It isn't really clear how to contribute to this bot at the moment. It is opened source, but due to the current CONTRIBUTING file point toward the main contributing docs this might disincentivize any contributions toward this bot. 

That might be by design though, I'm not sure 🤔
